The paper proposes an unsupervised domain adaptation model for multiple target domains with a labeled source domain. The model uses an information-theoretic approach to disentangle shared and private information among domains and find a common latent space. This work involves machine learning and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.MM sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses a problem of adapting to multiple domains, which is related to transfer learning and domain adaptation, covered in the cs.AI and cs.CL sub-categories.
